# tests Directory

This directory contains all test files for the project.

## Structure

```
tests/
├── __init__.py           # Make tests a package (Python)
├── conftest.py           # Shared fixtures (pytest)
├── unit/                 # Unit tests
│   └── test_*.py
├── integration/          # Integration tests
│   └── test_*.py
└── e2e/                  # End-to-end tests
    └── test_*.py
```

## Running Tests

### Python (pytest)
```bash
# All tests
pytest tests/ -v

# With coverage
pytest tests/ --cov=src --cov-report=html

# Specific test file
pytest tests/unit/test_module.py -v

# Run tests matching pattern
pytest tests/ -k "test_function_name"
```

### Node.js (Jest)
```bash
# All tests
npm test

# With coverage
npm run test:coverage

# Watch mode
npm run test:watch
```

### Go
```bash
# All tests
go test ./...

# With coverage
go test -cover ./...

# Verbose
go test -v ./...
```

## Test Naming Convention

- Test files: `test_<module>.py` (Python) or `<module>.test.ts` (TS)
- Test functions: `test_<function>_<scenario>` (Python) or `it('should <behavior>')` (TS)
- Test classes: `Test<ClassName>` (Python) or `describe('<ClassName>')` (TS)
